This paper discusses the design of a self-configuring routing scheme for spontaneous networks, which falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the use of hypercubes and multi-dimensional Cartesian spaces, which are commonly used in distributed computing (cs.DC) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the use of proactive and reactive routing protocols, which are commonly used in network security and information theory (cs.SI, cs.IT).
